            <span id="ChapterParagraphOne">
            <span id="BigFirstLetterText"></span>There was one couple in particular that we found in the Bridlington area. We would take the computer print-out, go down the list, and were expected to make a personal visit—to knock on doors—and find the members. One particular family attracted us because the parents had four sons. We thought, “Oh my. That would be wonderful to have a branch with four young men there.” So we went to their door two different times and rang the doorbell, but there was never anyone home. We kept going back.  <br />
            </span>

            <!--div id="ChapterPictureGallery" class="clearfix">
