            <div id="restofstory3" class="more">
                <span id="ChapterParagraphTwo">
                    I said, “Honey, we're supposed to make a personal visit. We're not just supposed to telephone.”  <br /><br /> 

                    He said, “We've been there twice, and they haven't been home. Just let me give them a call.” He picked up the phone, called them, and they picked up immediately. Brother Bird said, “We have been to your home twice and you haven't been home, and we just wanted to let you know about the branch being organized immediately.” <br /><br /> 

                    Brother Briggs said, “Our doorbell doesn't work.” <br /><br /> 

                    We were able to get them to come to church. They were very happy. When we visited their home, Sister Briggs welcomed me with a big hug, and with tears running down her cheeks, she said, “Brother and Sister Bird, where have you been? Where has the Church been? We haven't been involved for fifteen years.” <br /><br /> 

                    The Briggs were very active in the branch. Brother Briggs was called to be the branch president. We felt like he should be the branch president so he could have the experience that he needed when there would be no missionaries there. It was a happy experience with the Briggs. They became fast friends.<br /><br /> 

                    The little branch flourished. We were able to find members to come, and we held our meetings in a home for a month or two. Then we were able to rent a small building for our meetings. We had primary in the foyer of the little one-room building. Young people would come. We had a wonderful little branch that was established, and we were happy being able to help with that work. <br /><br /> 

                    One of the young men in the branch was about fifteen years old when we went to serve there. He was the primary teacher. When he became of missionary age, he put his missionary papers in and he was called to serve in the Pocatello Idaho Mission. He was ecstatic. He said he always wanted to serve in the United States, and he was hoping for Idaho. His prayers were definitely answered. It was a wonderful experience in that mission with wonderful members to get a branch started and the Church flourishing there. Now they have a new building, and we were happy to be able to participate in that.
