            <!--span id="ChapterParagraphTwo">
                We had been going out to visit one branch that was way up in the mountains out of Guatemala City. The road up there was a beautiful drive. It was a difficult road, but it was beautiful because there were bougainvillea flowers blossoming up there everywhere. We loved to drive up there and we looked forward to going. We would help the branch president, whoever was there who we could teach, and see if their reports were up to date. Then we would drive down the other side of the mountain. We had to ford a stream in order to get back into the city. 


            </span>
            <span id="SEE_MORE"><a href="#" id="restofstory4-show"  onclick="showHide('restofstory4');return false;">SEE MORE</a>
